1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Noah Shotwell for winning the one hundred twenty-kilogram Powerlifting
3 National Championship, East Regional Championship, and Division IV State
4 Championship and for being invited to represent the United States in the 2026 Junior
5 World Powerlifting Championships in South Africa.
6 WHEREAS, Noah Shotwell is a 2026 graduate of Slaughter Community Charter
7 School who is distinguished as the Powerlifting National Champion, East Regional
8 Champion, and Division IV State Champion in the one hundred twenty-kilogram weight
9 classification; and
10 WHEREAS, Mr. Shotwell completed a perfect powerlifting season with a three-lift
11 total of more than one thousand six hundred pounds and has cemented himself as the most
12 dominant powerlifter in Slaughter Community Charter School history; he holds the school's
13 overall records in squat, deadlift, and total weight; and
14 WHEREAS, Mr. Shotwell began powerlifting in high school and has established
15 himself as the strongest eighteen-year-old in the United States; and
16 WHEREAS, Mr. Shotwell received an invitation to represent the United States
17 during the 2026 World Championships in South Africa this August and will lift in the Junior
18 World Championship as part of the U.S. Junior National Team; and
19 WHEREAS, Mr. Shotwell has overcome physical struggles during his early life,
20 during which he spent years in pediatric physical and occupational therapy for low muscle
